          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1-1617029647012-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel and cut half your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into rough bite-sized pieces (save the rest for later!)</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>,<strong> garlic </strong>and<strong> ginger </strong>to a<strong> food processor </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong></p>",
